Hops & Grain







 


















Have a seat.What can we get you?
about our brewery





 








 










we are a part of ourCOMMUNITY

Community involvement should be at the heart of any small business. At Hops & Grain we are committed to being a good neighbor, not only to our planet but also to our neighborhood community. At both of our breweries we connect with other local businesses and non-profits to bring attention to what makes central Texas great, the creative men and women that live and work here! Each year our staff volunteers their time to work with our non-profit partners. In addition we donate our space and our product to help bring awareness to the great work that these partners are doing. After all, beer tends to bring out a crowd!


EAST AUSTIN ISUNIQUE IN ITS BLENDOF CULTURES



brewing sustainability




 








 








crafting a culture ofSUSTAINABILITY

Sustainability, by definition, is the endurance of systems and processes. At Hops & Grain we take sustainability very seriously. We focus our sustainability efforts in the areas of environmental stewardship, community involvement and industry leadership. We continually implement sustainable systems in our brewery. We're making our community greener through giving 1% of our annual revenue to local environmental non-profits and we support our local community growers and producers. We also make Brew Biscuit dog treats from our spent brewing grains and we package our beer in the most recyclable container on the planet, aluminum!


GOOD PLANETSARE HARD TO FIND

check out Brew Biscuits


visit our taproom




 








 








visiting ourTAPROOM
If you live in Austin, or are just in for a visit, our tap room is open 7 days a week from 10am – 10pm. Tours of the brewery are given Tuesday – Friday at 5pm and Saturday at 1, 3 and 5pm. Tours are FREE, last about 45 minutes. Saturdays we also have food trucks on-site. Dogs are welcome on our outdoor patio but are NOT allowed inside the tap room. More content to come...




