Why I Like Hops and Grain



I love Hops & Grain for so many reasons. It first starts with the beer which is delicious; the kind of delicious that brings a smile to your face. The Hops & Grain team continues to create new beers that amaze. Yet, as good as their products are; they are not the reason that Hops & Grain is a remarkable company.  As an investor, I have had first-hand exposure to how and why the Hops & Grain brand has been successful. It starts with Josh Hare, the CEO and founder who is committed to creating a culture that allows his employees to flourish. Josh embodies his company’s commitment to continually evolving. Early on, he discovered the importance of motivated employees and the power of an empowered workforce. He figured out that the more he could create an environment where his employees could make decisions; the more committed, engaged and passionate they became.    Hops & Grain is a special company for so many reasons. I love it for both what is inside the can and what that can represents.



Steve Wanta

                Investor in Hops & Grain (Austin) and Co-Founder / CEO at Just
                






THE BUZZ ABOUT HOPS AND GRAIN




Josh Hare isn’t your average beer brewer. The former triathlete has been brewing since he was 17, and the East Austin brewery that he runs with his wife, Meg, has already earned a strong reputation for great beer and a commitment to the environment.


