Brewing the Best Beer in Central Texas
People love our beer, but they also love our story. And that story is about community so we're expanding our community with a new tap room in San Marcos, TX.Rather than saying, “These are our beers, enjoy it or not.” We open our doors, invite people in, and hear what they want. There are aspects of our beer that scream Austin: because it was crafted by and for the people of Austin.




















The Beginning: Beers and Bikes
I started brewing beer since before I was legally able to enjoy it—in my college dorm room.  
        Since graduation, I’ve been a professional triathlete, helped found Rogue Running, and taught 7th grade science. But I never stopped thinking about beer. In 2011, I finally scratched that itch and opened Hops & Grain.
      
























Say Hello to Our Beers
I write all of our recipes myself, but it really starts from my conversations with our customers—they tell me what flavors they've been craving or the crazy ideas they have.  Our product lineup is a reflection of our biggest fans.






78702
78702 is brewed in the style of a traditional Kolsch. This German style brew is blonde in color, bright and clear with a lasting white foam head.  It has a refreshing medium hop bitterness upfront and clean and crisp finish. 



ALT-eration
Our 2012 World Beer Cup Gold Medal winning Altbier is brewed with old world techniques, quality German malts and noble hop varieties. It undergoes a multiple temperature mashing program to make a classic upfront maltiness with a clean, crisp finish.



Greenhouse IPA
The Greenhouse is a breeding ground. Each month we'll release around 300 cases per batch and each month we'll change the hop varieties that we use for dry-hopping in order to give you a different aroma and flavor experience with every new batch. 



Porter Culture
Our Baltic Porter starts with a base of Pilsner and Munich malts and we layer in chocolate wheat and de-bittered black malt to provide flavors of coffee, dark chocolate, raisins, and just a hint of roast. A neutral yeast profile lets the malts take center stage.





A Pale Mosaic
American style IPA showcasing a fairly new hop variety called Mosaic. The beer begins with a base of German Pale Ale and we dry-hop with Mosaic, Simcoe, and Nugget to deliver a clean and complex finish with notes of pine resin, grapefruit pith, and blueberries.



Pale Dog
Pale Dog is full of malt character with a dry, crisp, and hoppy finish. We start with a base of the highest quality 2 Row malted barley and blend with a small amount of Vienna and Caramel malts to add distinct character and a mouthful of hoppiness.



The One They Call Zoe
It’s similar to old world German lagers but dry-hopped to add an extra layer of complexity. Zoe is based on pale and vienna malts, with a beautiful white layer of foam resting on top, delivering floral and citrus dry-hop aromatics with every sip.




Our First Location: Austin, TX
We didn't anticipate the overwhelming response when we started selling our beer. We, almost overnight, were completely sold out. Having lived and fallen in love with Austin, I knew it was the perfect location for us. Our customers proved that gut feeling right.
 




  
    









Growth in Austin (Separate Entity, Same Brand)
Over the past two years we've increased revenue from under $60k per month to over $200,000 per month. We've also perfected our production processes, widened margins from 33% to 78%, and fostered a community of fun-loving, quality beer fans. We plan to replicate this model with our new entity in San Marcos.

Revenue graph for location 1. San Marcos location hasn't opened yet.









Invest in Our New Location (New Entity, Same H+G Brand)
Our Austin brewery is established. We've spent five years crafting high quality local beer at a great price. Now we're ready to expand with an all new tap room in San Marcos, TX, steps from Texas State University and 30,000 beer thirsty students.





  







Join Us for a Drink
May 17th, 2016It’s an exciting time to be a small business owner and an even more exciting time to be a small business owner in the craft beer industry!  We thrive as a brewery because our customers love to hear our story. That story revolves around our community and without that strong support base we wouldn’t be where we are today.  With that commitment to community, we’re incredibly excited to be able to raise funds for the next phase of our growth through this crowdfunding platform.  Enabling anyone interested to invest in our company, not just the wealthiest investors, is incredibly gratifying and truly encapsulates our company culture.  We are committed to brewing the highest quality beer that we can and serving it fresh for our customers to enjoy.  Quality beer is what has enabled our industry to experience rapid growth and we’re confident that our commitment to quality will enable us to sustain our growth into the future.  I’m very excited for the opportunity to involve you in our business and look forward to growing our community together.
Cheers!




Josh Hare
Founder & Managing Member
Hops & Grain Brewing 













